<TITLE> Ministries meet Monday over BDR trial </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)An inter-ministerial meeting will be held on Monday to decide how the BDR mutiny trial can be held soon and properly, the law minister said on Sunday. "The Supreme Court has already opined against the trial of the BDR mutiny under the Army Act. We will decide tomorrow's meeting under which law the trial can be held soonest," Shafique Ahmed told reporters at the Secretariat. The apex court returned its opinion on the presidential reference on Thursday saying that the BDR mutiny cannot be tried under army law. bdne
